00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,109
which is a public space
like a bus or train.

269
00:28:55,609 --> 00:28:56,769
I find it a bit out of line.

270
00:28:58,210 --> 00:28:59,940
This is understandable
nowadays.

271
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:01,509
It's not like I do this every day.

272
00:29:02,210 --> 00:29:03,809
"See one and you've seen them all."

273
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:06,119
How can you see all
after seeing just one?

274
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:08,990
It's hard to truly figure out a
person after seeing him or her once.

275
00:29:08,990 --> 00:29:10,289
We call this...

276
00:29:10,289 --> 00:29:13,319
the error of a hasty
generalization, Yoo Jung.

277
00:29:18,759 --> 00:29:19,859
Hey, Ji Hye.

278
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,329
You are very
disrespectful these days.

279
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:22,500
Do you know that?

280
00:29:28,839 --> 00:29:30,710
Mr. Lee, wait.

281
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:41,079
I definitely saw him from somewhere.

282
00:29:41,079 --> 00:29:42,250
Where did I see him?

283
00:29:43,819 --> 00:29:46,220
I can't seem to remember him. Gosh.

284
00:29:52,829 --> 00:29:54,960
Mr. Ji, you are distracting me.

285
00:29:56,470 --> 00:29:58,200
He's been like this
for the last few days.

286
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:00,240
He's looking for someone
whom he doesn't know.

287
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:04,539
That guy who was with
Prosecutor Cha just now...

288
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:06,680
Do you know who he is?

289
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:10,910
He's an arsonist.

290
00:30:10,910 --> 00:30:13,380
He's an arsonist? An arsonist...

291
00:30:14,750 --> 00:30:18,190
The witness who testified
for Kang Sun Il's case...

292
00:30:18,390 --> 00:30:19,690
- Ms. Eun.
- Yes?

293
00:30:19,819 --> 00:30:21,589
You are truly amazing.

294
00:30:27,299 --> 00:30:28,299
All right.

295
00:30:33,369 --> 00:30:34,539
I found him.

296
00:30:35,910 --> 00:30:37,009
His name is Lee Joon Hae.

297
00:30:38,910 --> 00:30:40,539
May I approach the witness,
Your Honor?

298
00:30:41,109 --> 00:30:43,410
(2 years ago)

299
00:30:45,619 --> 00:30:46,650
Witness.

300
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:49,450
At the time of the incident,

301
00:30:49,990 --> 00:30:52,089
you saw the person who got out
of the victim's house...

302
00:30:52,460 --> 00:30:54,259
during the fire and ran away, right?

303
00:30:54,390 --> 00:30:55,390
Yes.

304
00:30:56,460 --> 00:30:57,529
I did.

305
00:30:57,529 --> 00:31:01,660
The witness who stated that
he saw Kang Sun Il on the scene...

306
00:31:02,329 --> 00:31:04,329
- was Lee Joon Hae.
- He's sitting right there.

307
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:06,970
It was that man.

308
00:31:09,009 --> 00:31:11,769
He even attended the trial
as a witness.

309
00:31:12,079 --> 00:31:15,609
But he happened to be
an arsonist himself.

310
00:31:16,410 --> 00:31:17,849
Was it really a coincidence?

311
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:19,880
So to summarize it all,

312
00:31:20,380 --> 00:31:24,190
an arsonist witnessed an arson
and reported it to the police.

313
00:31:24,190 --> 00:31:25,519
It could've been a coincidence.

314
00:31:25,789 --> 00:31:27,720
- However...
- It's possible that it wasn't.

315
00:31:28,190 --> 00:31:30,059
If I was the prosecutor in charge,

316
00:31:30,390 --> 00:31:31,960
I would've considered him
one of the suspects...

317
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:33,029
You probably would have.

318
00:31:33,130 --> 00:31:35,569
I say that because many of those
who commit arson...

319
00:31:35,569 --> 00:31:37,670
seek heroism,
and that's why they start fires.

320
00:31:38,069 --> 00:31:40,569
"I'll start a fire and call the
police to become a hero."

321
00:31:40,569 --> 00:31:42,170
- Something like that.
- That's right.

322
00:31:42,369 --> 00:31:45,240
I've seen some of them
acting as if they're witnesses...

323
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:46,380
in the news.

324
00:31:46,380 --> 00:31:49,180
That's right.
I've heard of such cases too.

325
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:52,720
That's why the police make sure
to film the scene for arson cases.

326
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,250
It's highly likely that the arsonist
is one of the spectators.

327
00:31:55,750 --> 00:31:58,420
Then we should try to find
videos from the arson scene...

328
00:31:58,420 --> 00:32:00,259
or news clips related to the case.

329
00:32:00,519 --> 00:32:04,430
We should also go through the list
of petty arson cases in the area.

330
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:07,460
If our guess is right, his name will
very likely be on the list.

331
00:32:07,630 --> 00:32:09,269
Mr. Bang, please take care of it.

332
00:32:09,269 --> 00:32:13,000
Yes, you know a lot of people in
the police and the fire department.

333
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:14,140
- Please help us out.
- Gosh...

334
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:15,910
What's wrong?

335
00:32:15,910 --> 00:32:19,440
The stab wound is achy and itchy.

336
00:32:19,839 --> 00:32:20,940
I'm all right now.

337
00:32:21,180 --> 00:32:22,480
- Just take it easy, then.
- I...

338
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:23,480
- We'll take care of it.
- I'll do it.

339
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:25,380
- I'll do it.
- No, what are you talking about?

340
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:28,019
It's my job to take care of such
laborious tasks. I'll...

341
00:32:30,849 --> 00:32:32,660
I'm not getting a personal
secretary, driver,

342
00:32:32,660 --> 00:32:35,160
or an office manager, but I'll...

343
00:32:36,029 --> 00:32:37,289
- Let's find it ourselves.
- Okay.

344
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:38,730
- All right.
- I'll be back soon.

345
00:32:38,730 --> 00:32:40,299
- Okay.
- Take it easy, Mr. Bang.

346
00:32:40,299 --> 00:32:41,730
- Get some rest.
- I'm really okay.

347
00:32:41,730 --> 00:32:43,130
See you guys soon.

348
00:32:51,170 --> 00:32:53,339
I didn't think there would be
this many people who have...

349
00:32:53,410 --> 00:32:54,710
committed or attempted arson.

350
00:32:57,750 --> 00:32:58,880
I know, right?

351
00:32:59,180 --> 00:33:01,349
If Lee Joon Hae really was
the arsonist,

352
00:33:02,319 --> 00:33:04,349
Kang Sun Il, who's behind bars
right now, must be...

353
00:33:05,220 --> 00:33:06,589
extremely upset
at being falsely accused.

354
00:33:07,390 --> 00:33:09,529
He didn't even set the fire,

355
00:33:10,130 --> 00:33:11,759
yet he's been turned
into an arsonist and murderer.

356
00:33:13,430 --> 00:33:15,730
I'm not sure what to say. So far,

357
00:33:16,529 --> 00:33:19,269
no evidence that can prove
his innocence has turned up.

358
00:33:19,269 --> 00:33:20,940
We should dig more.

359
00:33:21,069 --> 00:33:25,240
I know.
But now, there's a possibility...

360
00:33:25,309 --> 00:33:27,480
that he may have been
falsely accused.

361
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:32,549
I know that, but I don't think you
should empathize too much.

362
00:33:33,450 --> 00:33:35,250
I'm not empathizing with him.

363
00:33:35,450 --> 00:33:38,960
I'm just trying to be fair
and keep all possibilities open.

364
00:33:39,319 --> 00:33:41,019
Well, from the way I see it,

365
00:33:41,759 --> 00:33:44,130
it looks like you're overly
empathizing with him.

366
00:33:44,430 --> 00:33:48,799
As an attorney, I don't think this
much empathy is excessive.

367
00:33:48,930 --> 00:33:50,630
- This is why attorneys...
- I know.

368
00:33:52,029 --> 00:33:53,099
You don't like them.

369
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:03,380
I'm sorry if I hurt your feelings.
I apologize.

370
00:34:06,579 --> 00:34:07,619
Me too.

371
00:34:28,809 --> 00:34:31,940
(Fire Station)

372
00:34:33,039 --> 00:34:34,679
Where's the next fire station?

373
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,010
Haeim Fire Station.

374
00:34:44,550 --> 00:34:46,320
Prosecutor Cha isn't here
at the moment.

375
00:34:50,059 --> 00:34:51,530
(Cha Yoo Jung)

376
00:34:52,559 --> 00:34:53,559
My gosh.

377
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:58,099
Hello, Mr. Ji.

378
00:34:58,429 --> 00:34:59,769
Hello, Prosecutor Na.

379
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:02,170
We've been running
into each other a lot lately.

380
00:35:02,570 --> 00:35:03,570
Yes, we have.

381
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:07,039
By the way,
have you seen Prosecutor Cha today?

382
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:09,409
Why do you need to see her?

383
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:11,110
Why do you think?
It's for work, of course.

384
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:15,989
Even if you don't emphasize
that it's for work,

385
00:35:16,650 --> 00:35:17,949
I won't get the wrong idea.

386
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:19,920
Pardon me?

387
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:22,230
You have her number, right?

388
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:23,960
Yes, of course.

389
00:35:24,389 --> 00:35:27,360
Yet you're making a point
of asking me about her.

390
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:35,269
Well... I have to take care of
something, so I should get going.

391
00:35:35,909 --> 00:35:37,510
All right.
I'll see you some other time.

392
00:35:37,570 --> 00:35:38,610
See you.

393
00:35:57,530 --> 00:35:58,690
You had a long day today.

394
00:35:59,460 --> 00:36:00,559
You should get some rest.

395
00:36:01,130 --> 00:36:02,230
Actually,

396
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:07,639
is there something you're
hiding from me?

397
00:36:11,769 --> 00:36:12,780
What?

398
00:36:14,639 --> 00:36:15,650
So there is.

399
00:36:17,250 --> 00:36:19,179
No, I'm not hiding anything.

400
00:36:22,050 --> 00:36:23,349
I'll believe you.

401
00:36:25,119 --> 00:36:26,159
Bong Hee.

402
00:36:27,860 --> 00:36:32,090
I keep wondering if I've done
something wrong. Have I?

403
00:36:34,659 --> 00:36:35,969
No, it's nothing like that.

404
00:36:36,300 --> 00:36:39,340
It's about me, not you. It's
something I need to work out myself.

405
00:36:41,539 --> 00:36:42,940
And I'm not allowed...

406
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:45,980
to ask you what it's about?

407
00:36:53,619 --> 00:36:54,679
All right.

408
00:37:36,730 --> 00:37:38,360
Is this another coincidence?

409
00:37:38,789 --> 00:37:41,500
No, it's not. I tried calling you,
but you didn't pick up.

410
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,170
Oh, you did?

411
00:37:43,769 --> 00:37:46,940
I don't check my phone often
because I rarely get calls.

412
00:37:47,269 --> 00:37:48,269
What's up?

413
00:37:48,539 --> 00:37:50,210
There's something I'd like to check.

414
00:37:51,469 --> 00:37:52,510
What is it?

415
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:54,010
It'll only take five minutes.

416
00:37:54,679 --> 00:37:56,949
I'm tired,
and my feet are killing me.

417
00:37:57,079 --> 00:37:59,780
I want to take these heels off
right now.

418
00:38:02,219 --> 00:38:04,119
- You can follow me if you want.
- What?

419
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:06,960
Hey.

420
00:38:32,980 --> 00:38:34,480
What is it that you want to check?

421
00:38:35,420 --> 00:38:38,989
Oh, right.
I'm working on an appeal case now.

422
00:38:39,159 --> 00:38:40,219
The witness of the case is...

423
00:38:40,219 --> 00:38:41,219
Lee Joon Hae?

424
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:45,829
Yes.

425
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:48,599
He's the one who attempted
the arson, isn't he?

426
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,869
And he's the culprit
of the case you're working on.

427
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:54,170
- What?
- He confessed.

428
00:38:54,269 --> 00:38:56,539
But the high-ups want me to bury it.

429
00:38:56,539 --> 00:38:58,139
That is complete nonsense.

430
00:39:04,079 --> 00:39:05,079
Here.

431
00:39:06,980 --> 00:39:07,980
What is this?

432
00:39:07,980 --> 00:39:09,719
I dug up some intel
on Lee Joon Hae.

433
00:39:10,389 --> 00:39:12,590
You can use it
for the trial if you'd like.

434
00:39:16,829 --> 00:39:17,860
Can you do this though?

435
00:39:18,190 --> 00:39:19,500
I don't even know.

436
00:39:20,929 --> 00:39:23,469
It's getting late.
You should get going if you're done.

437
00:39:24,269 --> 00:39:26,940
All right. Thanks for this.

438
00:39:27,369 --> 00:39:28,599
You can stay overnight if you want.

439
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:30,840
What?

440
00:39:31,239 --> 00:39:32,239
I was joking.

441
00:39:32,739 --> 00:39:34,539
How can you make such a joke?

442
00:39:34,539 --> 00:39:36,280
You think I'm a witch no matter what
I do.

443
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:38,079
Doesn't the joke suit me perfectly?

444
00:39:38,550 --> 00:39:39,550
No.

445
00:39:40,619 --> 00:39:43,550
Hey, Yoo Jung.
Stop beating yourself up.

446
00:39:44,889 --> 00:39:45,889
It's not good for you.

447
00:39:51,989 --> 00:39:53,300
Anyway,

448
00:39:55,300 --> 00:39:56,869
why didn't you tell Ji Wook...

449
00:39:57,429 --> 00:39:58,429
that nothing...

450
00:39:59,070 --> 00:40:00,170
happened on that night?

451
00:40:02,199 --> 00:40:03,940
Whether it was a mistake or not,

452
00:40:05,539 --> 00:40:07,510
it is true that something
could have...

453
00:40:07,510 --> 00:40:08,539
happened on that night.

454
00:40:11,179 --> 00:40:12,179
I see.

455
00:40:14,519 --> 00:40:15,519
Then what about you?

456
00:40:17,090 --> 00:40:18,349
Why didn't you tell him?

457
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,289
Because it is true that I...

458
00:40:24,159 --> 00:40:25,260
hurt him.

459
00:40:54,159 --> 00:40:55,260
Yes, Mr. Bang.

460
00:41:09,039 --> 00:41:10,940
I'm still a bachelor.

461
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:14,139
I can't believe I have a stab
wound on my stomach.

462
00:41:14,809 --> 00:41:19,179
I'm so worried that I wouldn't
be able to meet someone.

463
00:41:24,019 --> 00:41:25,619
What do you guys think about this?

464
00:41:28,159 --> 00:41:29,360
Well, I think...

465
00:41:30,059 --> 00:41:31,630
it's great.

466
00:41:31,630 --> 00:41:32,829
I love it.

467
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,429
Right.

468
00:41:34,929 --> 00:41:36,170
I think it's going to be okay.

469
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:38,900
What's great?

470
00:41:39,170 --> 00:41:40,969
What is so great and will be okay?

471
00:41:43,969 --> 00:41:45,010
I'm sorry.

472
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:46,880
Me too.

473
00:41:48,610 --> 00:41:51,409
What are you two so worried about?

474
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:55,420
I'm not married, and yet I'm raising
four adults. I'm drinking...

475
00:41:55,420 --> 00:41:58,090
soda because I was stabbed
in the stomach.

476
00:41:58,849 --> 00:42:01,619
Why do you look so down?
Your lives are not that bad.

477
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:06,460
I think I made a mistake.

478
00:42:07,099 --> 00:42:09,159
Everything is my fault.

479
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:13,170
It's my fault too.

480
00:42:14,199 --> 00:42:15,199
Gosh.

481
00:42:16,170 --> 00:42:18,170
Why are you apologizing?

482
00:42:18,940 --> 00:42:22,139
To be honest, you two are in a bind.

483
00:42:22,179 --> 00:42:23,250
Then...

484
00:42:23,510 --> 00:42:25,250
what should I do?

485
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:28,179
It seems like I'm out of options.

486
00:42:28,179 --> 00:42:31,619
Mr. Bang, you should tell
me what I should do.

487
00:42:31,650 --> 00:42:32,659
- Goodness.
- Please?

488
00:42:33,090 --> 00:42:34,559
Give me advice for me first.

489
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,260
I can't figure this out.

490
00:43:04,949 --> 00:43:06,920
Unbelievable. Mr. Bang!

491
00:43:07,090 --> 00:43:10,059
You got your stitches only recently.
How can you drink like this?

492
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:11,760
Goodness,

493
00:43:12,090 --> 00:43:14,059
why are you crying?
Are you that drunk?

494
00:43:15,900 --> 00:43:17,170
I drank soda.

495
00:43:17,769 --> 00:43:19,539
Do you think I'd believe that?

496
00:43:19,539 --> 00:43:21,739
What kind of person cries
after drinking soda?

497
00:43:21,739 --> 00:43:23,269
- Goodness, you are in trouble.
- Wait.

498
00:43:23,269 --> 00:43:26,440
It's Bong Hee. Hey,
Bong Hee. Bong Hee!

499
00:43:28,079 --> 00:43:29,139
Have a glass.

500
00:43:29,750 --> 00:43:30,909
It is soda.

501
00:43:31,449 --> 00:43:33,179
- Have 2 glasses.
- No, have only 1.

502
00:43:33,449 --> 00:43:34,650
Bong Hee, have one.

503
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:37,090
- Take 2 glasses.
- No, have just 1.

504
00:43:37,090 --> 00:43:38,519
Since she's late, take two glasses.

505
00:43:38,519 --> 00:43:40,090
Since she's late, take one glass.

506
00:43:40,519 --> 00:43:41,619
Fine. Take three then.

507
00:43:43,760 --> 00:43:44,789
Goodness.

508
00:43:44,989 --> 00:43:46,030
Gosh.

509
00:43:46,429 --> 00:43:47,900
- Let's go.
- Okay.

510
00:43:47,929 --> 00:43:49,030
- We're going.
- Another round?

511
00:43:49,030 --> 00:43:51,099
- No, no.
- Don't do that.

512
00:43:51,099 --> 00:43:52,630
- This way.
- It's my fault.

513
00:43:53,099 --> 00:43:54,469
Be careful.

514
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,840
I'm all right.

515
00:43:57,510 --> 00:44:00,510
Hold on. Just sit here for a while.

516
00:44:00,510 --> 00:44:01,639
Let me bring you some water.

517
00:44:14,519 --> 00:44:15,559
We...

518
00:44:17,460 --> 00:44:19,829
should never break up, Bong Hee.

519
00:44:22,969 --> 00:44:24,530
Even if I tell you to leave me,

520
00:44:25,769 --> 00:44:26,800
don't leave.

521
00:44:30,809 --> 00:44:31,840
We...

522
00:44:34,610 --> 00:44:35,940
should only think about ourselves.

523
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:42,050
Don't leave me.

524
00:44:43,519 --> 00:44:44,619
Please?

525
00:44:51,090 --> 00:44:52,090
I won't.

526
00:44:52,630 --> 00:44:53,630
Don't worry.

527
00:45:35,170 --> 00:45:37,840
Mr. Byun hid those because
he wanted to have them to himself.

528
00:45:42,510 --> 00:45:44,150
I can eat them all in secret...

