00:48:04,789 --> 00:48:05,789
No.

572
00:48:06,289 --> 00:48:08,360
Lee Joon Hae is the arsonist.

573
00:48:10,030 --> 00:48:11,159
I have an informant.

574
00:48:11,260 --> 00:48:13,630
That's great, but until the end,

575
00:48:13,630 --> 00:48:16,469
we shouldn't conclude
whether he's guilty or not.

576
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:18,000
Let's take a look first.

577
00:48:19,030 --> 00:48:20,940
I have the photos of the scene.

578
00:48:21,800 --> 00:48:22,769
Will you be okay?

579
00:48:25,409 --> 00:48:26,409
Yes, I'll be.

580
00:48:38,750 --> 00:48:40,820
There were countless hints.

581
00:48:41,559 --> 00:48:42,619
Why...

582
00:48:43,159 --> 00:48:44,760
hadn't I figured it out?

583
00:48:46,059 --> 00:48:47,929
(Currently under trial)

584
00:48:57,539 --> 00:49:00,880
Witness, I believe you know
quite a lot about xylene.

585
00:49:01,340 --> 00:49:03,650
Excuse me? What is that?

586
00:49:04,909 --> 00:49:06,280
According to my research,

587
00:49:06,280 --> 00:49:09,420
I'm aware that your occupation
is related to producing...

588
00:49:09,420 --> 00:49:12,019
paints, varnish, and
adhesives at Cheonho Chemicals.

589
00:49:12,019 --> 00:49:13,019
Am I mistaken?

590
00:49:13,659 --> 00:49:15,360
In the process of producing
these chemicals,

591
00:49:15,559 --> 00:49:16,829
xylene is used.

592
00:49:18,030 --> 00:49:19,030
Oh, that.

593
00:49:20,059 --> 00:49:21,159
I think so.

594
00:49:22,630 --> 00:49:26,469
Xylene is considered to be
a very strong inflammable material.

595
00:49:27,099 --> 00:49:28,139
Moreover,

596
00:49:28,139 --> 00:49:30,539
it was also used to cause a fire
in Doboo-dong two years ago...

597
00:49:30,840 --> 00:49:32,239
by the arsonist.

598
00:49:33,940 --> 00:49:36,210
By any chance, were you
aware of this fact?

599
00:49:36,610 --> 00:49:38,650
No, I didn't know that.

600
00:49:39,010 --> 00:49:40,119
Is that so?

601
00:49:41,619 --> 00:49:43,389
Then how should I explain this?

602
00:49:49,360 --> 00:49:50,690
Mr. Lee Joon Hae...

603
00:49:51,030 --> 00:49:54,400
recently got arrested by the police
for...

604
00:49:54,530 --> 00:49:56,369
attempted incendiarism.

605
00:49:56,530 --> 00:50:01,239
But a female prosecutor
just told me to leave back then.

606
00:50:01,239 --> 00:50:04,469
The police confiscated the flammable
material from Mr. Lee,

607
00:50:04,469 --> 00:50:06,239
and they requested a
component analysis.

608
00:50:07,139 --> 00:50:10,449
According to the analysis,
it contained a mixture of xylene.

609
00:50:11,309 --> 00:50:12,579
They also did a comparative
analysis...

610
00:50:13,050 --> 00:50:16,849
with the material that caused
the fire two years ago.

611
00:50:17,750 --> 00:50:20,659
The result showed that the two
flammables were almost identical.

612
00:50:26,030 --> 00:50:29,329
There are times when you come
to a sudden realization.

613
00:50:47,750 --> 00:50:49,750
Excuse me. I have to go somewhere.

614
00:51:20,150 --> 00:51:21,250
Hey, Mom.

615
00:51:24,050 --> 00:51:25,750
I attended a trial today.

616
00:51:28,119 --> 00:51:29,389
There was this man...

617
00:51:30,260 --> 00:51:33,260
who was falsely accused of
murder and arson.

618
00:51:35,260 --> 00:51:37,869
Fortunately, it looks like...

619
00:51:38,630 --> 00:51:41,139
the appeal trial will lead to a
positive result.

620
00:51:42,139 --> 00:51:44,010
So I think it'll all turn out well.

621
00:51:44,440 --> 00:51:45,469
Really?

622
00:51:46,210 --> 00:51:48,539
Yes. Really.

623
00:51:50,579 --> 00:51:52,349
So I feel great right now.

624
00:51:55,420 --> 00:51:57,050
I just wanted to tell you this.

625
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:03,159
But...

626
00:52:05,059 --> 00:52:06,389
But Mom...

627
00:52:06,860 --> 00:52:08,360
Yes? What is it?

628
00:52:11,969 --> 00:52:13,130
Well...

629
00:52:14,570 --> 00:52:15,599
Never mind.

630
00:52:17,570 --> 00:52:19,239
I'm busy right now,

631
00:52:19,940 --> 00:52:23,250
so I'll call you again later.
I'm going to hang up now.

632
00:52:35,760 --> 00:52:38,789
How could I not have known?

633
00:52:55,010 --> 00:52:58,849
("A Prosecutor Couple Died
in an Unfortunate Revenge Arson")

634
00:53:06,619 --> 00:53:10,760
I read the article regarding my
dad's accident so many times...

635
00:53:11,159 --> 00:53:13,960
that I practically memorized
the story of the victim's family.

636
00:53:13,960 --> 00:53:15,329
(8-year-old son, involved in an
assault incident, prosecutor couple)

637
00:53:16,699 --> 00:53:18,429
Ji Wook and his parents...

638
00:53:19,130 --> 00:53:21,070
were supposed to go on
a family picnic...

639
00:53:21,969 --> 00:53:24,309
on the day after his dad
had passed away.

640
00:53:25,369 --> 00:53:28,110
The anniversary date of
both our fathers' deaths.

641
00:53:28,110 --> 00:53:30,050
(No Young Suk, June 15, 1994)

642
00:53:30,050 --> 00:53:32,110
(Eun Man Soo, June 15, 1994)

643
00:53:32,110 --> 00:53:35,949
I lost both my parents in a
fire accident when I was young.

644
00:53:37,150 --> 00:53:38,849
My dad passed away first.

645
00:53:39,650 --> 00:53:42,960
My mom got transported to
a hospital,

646
00:53:43,659 --> 00:53:44,960
but she passed away...

647
00:53:46,059 --> 00:53:47,329
not too soon after that.

648
00:53:49,030 --> 00:53:52,670
Ji Wook, why did you become
a prosecutor?

649
00:53:54,139 --> 00:53:55,239
My dad...

650
00:53:56,239 --> 00:53:57,369
was a prosecutor.

651
00:53:58,570 --> 00:54:00,440
I guess you wanted to
become like your dad.

652
00:54:03,849 --> 00:54:04,849
Yes.

653
00:54:23,130 --> 00:54:24,329
Good work, Ji Wook.

654
00:54:24,599 --> 00:54:26,170
- Thanks. See you.
- Okay.

655
00:54:31,940 --> 00:54:35,039
Thank you. I think I'll win
this case thanks to you.

656
00:54:35,210 --> 00:54:36,380
Of course.

657
00:54:38,610 --> 00:54:39,880
Will you be okay?

658
00:54:41,050 --> 00:54:43,789
Well, I didn't let go of the case
like they told me to,

659
00:54:43,789 --> 00:54:45,250
so I'm guessing I'll just get
chewed out.

660
00:54:47,860 --> 00:54:51,130
But I'm never going to quit
my job...

661
00:54:51,630 --> 00:54:53,159
because you guys refused to
take me in.

662
00:55:05,210 --> 00:55:06,239
Hey, Bong Hee.

663
00:55:06,940 --> 00:55:08,780
I couldn't find you, so I was
wondering if you already left.

664
00:55:09,139 --> 00:55:11,010
I was reminded of something urgent.

665
00:55:12,409 --> 00:55:14,949
I see. It's nothing serious, right?

666
00:55:15,780 --> 00:55:18,750
Okay. I'll wait for you at home.

